The paper deals with the problem of embedding heterogeneous information networks, which is a common topic in several sub-fields of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on personalized preferences and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
